post_text:
The New York State Public High School Athletic Association (NYSPHSAA) voted to delay the official start date of the Fall 2020 sports season, cancel the Fall 2020 Regional and State Championships and prepare to implement a condensed season schedule in January 2021 if high school sports remain prohibited throughout 2020 due to COVID-19. The NYSPHSAA Officers’ decision includes:

• Delay Fall sports start date until Monday, September 21st (NYSPHSAA PAUSE)
• Cancel Fall Regional and State Championship events
• Waive seven-day practice rule
• Maintain current practice requirements
• Encourage geographic scheduling for games & contests
text:
The New York State Public High School Athletic Association (NYSPHSAA) voted to delay the official start date of the Fall 2020 sports season, cancel the Fall 2020 Regional and State Championships and prepare to implement a condensed season schedule in January 2021 if high school sports remain prohibited throughout 2020 due to COVID-19. The NYSPHSAA Officers’ decision includes:

• Delay Fall sports start date until Monday, September 21st (NYSPHSAA PAUSE)
• Cancel Fall Regional and State Championship events
• Waive seven-day practice rule
• Maintain current practice requirements
• Encourage geographic scheduling for games & contests

post_text:
Closure & Meal Updates - Regents Exams Cancelled

Morristown CSD will continue to be closed until at least April 29th.

Regents Exams for June 2020 have been cancelled. A student scheduled to take a Regents Exam shall be exempted from that exam provided that the student passes the course by the end of this school year.

Food distribution will continue today, April 8th and tomorrow, April 9th by bus route and will be available for village students in the Bus Loop from 11:00 am--12:30 pm. The April 9th delivery will include groceries to cover five days of breakfast/lunch meals.

Five day breakfast/lunch meals will continue to be available April 20th and April 27th.

Five day breakfast/lunch meals will continue to be available April 20th and April 27th.

This is a reminder that MCS will begin delivering lunch and breakfast for children 18 and under on Monday, 3/23/20. Buses will leave MCS at 11 a.m. to make deliveries between 11 a.m. - 12 p.m. Please let us know if you have preschool age children who are currently not attending school so we can prepare meals for them as well. Parents who wish to OPT out of this program, please call the Main Office so the District does not prepare food that is not needed.

We will also be delivering packets for all students for their classes on Monday. On Wednesday, we plan to deliver Chromebooks for students in Gr. 5-12 who were unable to pick one up on Saturday.

Please be patient as we work to try to meet everyone's needs!

Due to the most recent directive from the Governor, MCS will only be able to retrieve student locker contents TODAY, Friday, March 20th, until 3 p.m. Please call by 2:15 so that we have time to pack things.

Chromebooks will be issued tomorrow - Saturday, March 21, using the posted schedule on both our website and Facebook page. It is imperative that everyone follows this schedule.

8::00 - 9:30 a.m.:
Grade 12 will be distributed at the Main Entrance.
Grade 11 will be distributed at the Bus Loop entrance by Mr. Wills’s room.
Grade 10 will be distributed at the Bus Loop Art Room entrance.

9:30 - 11:00 a.m.:
Grade 9 will be distributed at the Main Entrance.
Grade 8 will be distributed at the Bus Loop entrance by Mr. Wills’s room.
Grade 7 will be distributed at the Bus Loop Art Room entrance.

11:00 a.m - 12:00 p.m.:
Grade 6 will be distributed at the Main Entrance.
Grade 5 will be distributed at the Bus Loop entrance by Mr. Wills’s room.

*Students without home Wi-Fi/Internet access will need to log in at school to activate the Google Drive app to have access to Google files at home.

From SUNY Canton Baseball:

"The SUNY Canton baseball team will host its winter clinics on four different days in January, February and March clinics are for ages 8 to 18.

The clinics cost $30 each or $100 if a player attends all four days. All clinics will take place at the Roos House on the campus of SUNY Canton.

The clinics will take place on January 26th, February 9th and 16th and March 1st. All clinics will run from 5-7:30 p.m. each day.

If you are interested in signing up for the clinic please e-mail Head Coach Joe Carbone at carbonej@canton.edu or call him at 315-600-0752."

post_text:
MCS teacher Jennifer Collins will offer the NYS accepted CPR and First Aid certification classes need to coach youth sports. Both classes will given at MCS in Room 125.

1. The CPR portion will be offered on Tuesday, 11/5, at 4:30 p.m. and will take approximately 3-4 hours to complete - including skills testing. The cost of the class will be $45 and includes a pocket mask to keep.

2. The First Aid portion will be offered on Wednesday, 11/6, at 4:30 p.m. and will take a full 4 hours to complete. It is a refresher of emergency situations and you will need to demonstrate a few of the skills taught. The cost of this class is $40.

If you will be attending both classes the cost will be $80. Jenn can accept cash, credit cards, and checks (made out to: Hero's Haven).

If you are interested in attending, please RSVP by Monday, 11/4, at 11 a.m. Call 315-244-4341 or email jenn@heros-haven.com.

URGENT: North Country Child Care Crisis Survey

The St. Lawrence Public Health Department is asking parents, guardians, and caregivers with children under the age of 8 years to help us at St. Lawrence Child Care Council. We would like to gather information on your experience(s) trying to find child care, the current cost of child care, and work related challenges you or family members have experienced because of child care issues. Your answers will provide important information that can be used help address the critical shortage of child care throughout North Country school districts. The survey is available online and will only take a few minutes to complete—please see the link below. All answers will be kept anonymous and confidential. If you have any questions please contact the St. Lawrence Child Care Council at (315) 393-6474. Thank you for your participation!

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/NCChildCareFamilies
